40|$|Newscaster is an {{architecture}} {{and a set}} of protocols for distributing Usenet Netnews via IP multicast enabled networks. The architecture is designed to be useful in the global Internet. In particular, it allows multiple <b>news</b> <b>servers</b> to cooperate on multicasting each new article only once. To facilitate scalability {{to tens of thousands of}} <b>news</b> <b>servers,</b> it also provides for receive-only multicast participants (that continue to send articles via conventional NNTP). First results from an experiment using the Newscaster system for global news distribution are reported. 1...|$|R
50|$|A newsreader, {{also known}} as a news client, is a {{software}} application that reads articles on Usenet, either directly from the <b>news</b> <b>server's</b> disks or via the NNTP.|$|R
