50|$|C News is a <b>news</b> <b>server</b> package, {{written by}} Geoff Collyer, {{assisted}} by Henry Spencer, at the University of Toronto {{as a replacement}} for B News. It was presented at the Winter 1987 USENIX conference in Washington, D.C.|$|E
50|$|Some servers, such as INN, allow {{multiple}} storage {{schemes to}} be used at once. Various hybrid storage schemes have also been used in <b>news</b> <b>servers,</b> including different organizations of the file-per-article method, or smaller containers carrying perhaps 100 articles apiece.|$|R
50|$|Usenet was {{originally}} designed {{based on the}} UUCP network, with most article transfers taking place over direct point-to-point telephone links between <b>news</b> <b>servers,</b> which were powerful time-sharing systems. Readers and posters logged into these computers reading the articles directly from the local disk.|$|R
